13/08/2004
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Mayors from Southeast European countries met to discuss regional co-operation issues in Thessaloniki on Thursday (12 August).
Talks focused on possible joint projects -- potentially eligible for EU financing -- within the Major Balkan Cities Network, and on co-operation in the fields of sports and culture.
According to the Greek press, participants expressed support for Thessaloniki's bid to host the EXPO 2008 international exhibition.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 13/08/04;
MPA - 12/08/04)
